{
  "id": 5861138256494592,
  "name": "Enable monochrome emoji rendering in forced colors mode.",
  "summary": "This change updates Chromium’s emoji rendering behavior in Forced Colors Mode. During computed-value resolution, emoji whose font-variant-emoji value computes to normal or unicode are rendered using their monochrome glyphs when available.\n\nChromium will therefore suppress color emoji rendering, which ensures emojis fully participate in the Forced Colors Mode pipeline and respect system high-contrast colors. Behavior outside forced colors mode is unchanged.",
